Issues.Body:
* .NET Core Version: .Net 3.0 SDK Preview8 013656 build
* Have you experienced this same bug with .NET Framework?: Yes

**Repro Steps:**
1. Create a Winforms .Net Core application

2. Add DataGridView control, set ReadOnly property to true

3. Add columns and rows

    public Form1()
        {
            InitializeComponent();
            this.dataGridView1.ReadOnly = true;
            this.dataGridView1.Rows.Insert(0, new object[3] { "aa", "bb", "cc" });
            this.dataGridView1.Rows.Insert(0, new object[3] { "aa1", "bb1", "cc1" });
        }

4. Run app and navigate to a cell in narrator or check the Value.IsReadOnly property in Inspect 
[WindowsFormsApp5.zip](https://github.com/dotnet/winforms/files/3475785/WindowsFormsApp5.zip)

**Actual behavior:**
In Narrator, it reads the cell with editing state. And in Inspect, its Value.IsReadyOnly is false. Please see following screenshot:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26474449/62604294-9f6b3600-b8ac-11e9-8254-745fc1fec9c9.png)

**Expected behavior:**
In Narrator, it should announce the cell with ReadOnly state, and In Inspect, Value.IsReadOnly property should be true when focusing on cell.
